Nigeria Seeks U.S. Investors to Boost Agricultural Industry, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-31T08:20:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/nigeria-seeks-u-s-investors-to-boost-agricultural-industry-thisday-says.html
Nigeria is seeking U.S. investors to
help boost agricultural output in the West African nation,
 ThisDay reported , citing David Adejuwon, director of trade at
the Ministry of Commerce and Industry.  The Nigerian government wants to boost crop and livestock
production as well as its agricultural storage and management
capability, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  